  "meter": "4/4",
  "bpm": 100,
  "words": "verses 1-3, Samuel Davies, 1769. alt. verses 4-6, Brian J. Dumont, 15 Nov 2010",
  "music": "Henry K. Oliver, 1832",
  "tune": "Federal Street",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "While o&#39;er our guilty land, O Lord, We view the terrors of Your sword, O where can all the helpless fly? To whom but You direct their cry?",
    "v2": "On You, our guardian God, we call; Before Your throne of grace we fall; But is there no deliv&#39;rance there? And must we perish in despair?",
    "v3": "See, we repent, we weep, we mourn; To our forsaken God we turn; O spare our guilty country, spare The Church which You have planted there.",
    "v4": "We are the old, the sick, the lame; We blind and deaf cry Jesus&#39; Name. We plead Your mercy for His sake, And trust that You will not forsake.",
    "v5": "Christ is our only righteousness, His death for us is our redress. Your promise stronger than our sin; Blot out O Lord what we have been."
  },
